[INCLUDE:Engine/Rendering/LightingAndShadows/LightFunctions#LightFunctions]

Since you are primarily using Light Functions to change the overall shape of a light, it is possible to confuse them with IES profiles, which are shown in [Example 3.1](Resources\ContentExamples\Lighting\3_1). However, IES profiles are significantly cheaper to calculate, and should be used instead of Light Functions whenever possible.





